<paragraph id="8B9F3697DF7D110FFF15CABFFD541D2E" blockId="4.[151,1436,454,1988]" pageId="4" pageNumber="64">
Cespitose perennials with erect culms. Leaf sheaths hirsute, fibrous and persistent after senescence, leaf blades flat, flexuous, pale, silvery-hirsute. Racemes paired or solitary, 
<quantity id="4CD89B72DF7D110FFC65CA94FBEF1D52" box="[999,1110,493,519]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="64" unit="cm" value="2.75" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–4 cm</quantity>
long, with rachis narrowly winged, not covering the spikelets. Spikelets paired, subglabrous, lower glumes 5–7-nerved, up to ¾ the length of the spikelets; upper glumes obovate, cucullate, 11-nerved; lower floret usually male, the lower lemma 9-nerved, glume-like; upper floret bisexual.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33A651CDF7D110EFF44C9FEFA8E1DD4" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="65" pageId="4" pageNumber="64" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B9F3697DF7D110FFF44C9FEFD791CDF" blockId="4.[151,1436,454,1988]" pageId="4" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis id="B954EA85DF7D110FFF44C9FEFCA81DF4" bold="true" box="[198,785,647,673]" pageId="4" pageNumber="64">Distribution, habitat, and conservation status:</emphasis>
―Endemic from the Brazilian states of 
<collectingRegion id="49E4F875DF7D110FFB77C9F1FA2E1DF7" box="[1269,1431,648,674]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="4" pageNumber="64">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49E4F875DF7D110FFF15C9D7FEB71D9D" box="[151,270,686,712]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="4" pageNumber="64">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
(most ancient collections known from both states), and 
<collectingRegion id="49E4F875DF7D110FFC2AC9D7FC451D9D" box="[936,1020,686,712]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="4" pageNumber="64">Paraná</collectingRegion>
. This species has been consistently collected near Ponta Grossa (state of 
<collectingRegion id="49E4F875DF7D110FFDD6C9ACFD1F1DBA" box="[596,678,725,751]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="4" pageNumber="64">Paraná</collectingRegion>
) in the vicinity of Vila Velha (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B66DF7D110FFB91C9ACFB051DBA" author="Burman, A. G." box="[1043,1212,725,751]" pageId="4" pageNumber="64" pagination="101 - 116" refId="ref3666" refString="Burman, A. G. (1983) The genus Thrasyopsis Parodi (Gramineae). Phyton (Austria) 23: 101 - 116." type="journal article" year="1983">Burman 1983</bibRefCitation>
). Nevertheless, we have recently conducted intensive field collections in this area and only found a single tuft. Although the current conservation status of this species has not yet been established, it is very likely to be a threatened species, because of its extreme rarity. Flowering of 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D14DF7D110FFD77C830FC511C37" authorityName="G. H. Rua &amp; Valls" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Nees" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[757,1000,841,866]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Paspalum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="repandum">
<emphasis id="B954EA85DF7D110FFD77C830FC511C37" box="[757,1000,841,866]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="64">Paspalum repandum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be fire-dependent, since all known herbarium specimens are burned plants.
</paragraph>
